    "id": 3448873,
    "postDate": "2026-04-26T20:58:32.093Z",
    "rawMarkdown": "The original model from the post didn't pass the shapes check from [this comment](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/neurogolf-2026/discussion/693711#3447781).\n\nHowever, there is a way around it: add explicit static `value_info` for the tensors after `Compress`, so ONNX `infer_shapes()` reports concrete shapes for the static-shape check while `onnx-tool` ignores those annotations and still profiles the same tensors as zero-batch via its fake-zero `Compress` inference.\n\nAttaching updated model which still scores `25.00` on task 1.",
    "content": "<p>The original model from the post didn't pass the shapes check from <a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/neurogolf-2026/discussion/693711#3447781\" target=\"_blank\">this comment</a>.</p>\n<p>However, there is a way around it: add explicit static <code>value_info</code> for the tensors after <code>Compress</code>, so ONNX <code>infer_shapes()</code> reports concrete shapes for the static-shape check while <code>onnx-tool</code> ignores those annotations and still profiles the same tensors as zero-batch via its fake-zero <code>Compress</code> inference.</p>\n<p>Attaching updated model which still scores <code>25.00</code> on task 1.</p>",
